<DIV class=3D"PaddingLeft5" id=3D"div2"><BR><FONT size=3D"2">
<P align=3D"justify">
<DIV>The scope of this document is to describe integration of SAP Web =
Services=20
and Microsoft .NET using Microsoft Visual Studio.</DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV><B>SAP WEB SERVICES AND VISUAL STUDIO .NET ARCHITECTURE AND=20
OVERVIEW</B></DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV><B>BACK GROUND</B></DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV>SAP and Microsoft .NET can be integrated via couple of options. On =
the top:=20
SAP Web Services can be consumed in a straight line in .NET web client, =
ASP.NET.=20
ASP.NET has built in support for the consuming Web Service WSDL and =
generating=20
the proxy code. Once we have the proxy code, that can be consumed in any =
.NET=20
client applications like console application, web application, WCF=20
application.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV><IMG width=3D"314" height=3D"297" alt=3D"1.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/1.gif"=20
border=3D"0"><BR></DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV><B>USING VISUAL STUDIO.NET TO GENERATE PROXY FROM SAP WEB =
SERVICE</B></DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV>There two steps involved the creation of the proxy. First create a =
wsdl for=20
the given web service and then generate the proxy by consuming the WSDL. =
I will=20
let you the reason behind it.</DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV><B>A.</B>&nbsp;Creating WSDL from the Web Service URL.</DIV>
<DIV>
<OL>
  <LI>Open the Internet explorer and input the web service URL that is =
created=20
  in SAP server and click enter. Enter the credentials when it asks for. =
And=20
  click on OK button<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"323" height=3D"58" =
alt=3D"2.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/2.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>It will generate the WSDL for the web service<BR><BR><IMG =
width=3D"509"=20
  height=3D"269" alt=3D"3.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/3.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Save the WSDL file to the disk with the WSDL extension and open =
the WSDL=20
  in .NET IDE or in the notepad.<BR><BR>Find the 'System' in the WSDL =
and=20
  replace with "SYSTEM" because the namespace System is already reserved =
in=20
  Visual Studio. If you do not change the name of this element here to =
all=20
  capital letters, you will get errors when building the =
application.<BR><BR>The=20
  next change you need to make on the WSDL is to rename all instances of =

  "parameters" to "parameter." This is necessary to be able to read the =
methods=20
  of the Web service correctly in Visual Studio. Save the changes for =
further=20
  use to generate the proxy.&nbsp;<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"489" =
height=3D"301" alt=3D"4.gif"=20
  =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/4.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"></LI></OL></DIV>
<DIV><B>B.</B>&nbsp;In the second step, Follow the steps to generate the =
proxy=20
for client.</DIV>
<DIV>
<OL>
  <LI>Open up the Microsoft Visual Studio any version. Create a blank =
solution=20
  with the same if SAPDotNetIntegration.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Create a new class library project, by adding a new project to the =

  solution. Name it is SAPWebServiceProxyLibrary. &nbsp;The purpose of =
creating=20
  it as separate library is the it can be reference in .net client =
application=20
  for use.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Right click oin the SAPWebServiceProxyLibrary project and click on =
'Add=20
  web referance' context menu.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Enter the Disk path of the WSDL generated in the first step in the =
URL=20
  drop down and click on 'Go' button.&nbsp;<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"350" =
height=3D"249"=20
  alt=3D"5.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/5.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>System shows the following screen.<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"367" =
height=3D"261"=20
  alt=3D"6.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/6.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Click on the 'Allow block content' as shown below. Which show the=20
  generated WSDL.<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"364" height=3D"258" alt=3D"7.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/7.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR><IMG width=3D"364" height=3D"260" alt=3D"8.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/8.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Enter 'SAPWebServiceNamespace' in the 'Web reference name' text =
box and=20
  click on 'Add Referance' button. Which will generate the .NET proxy =
class of=20
  the client to consume.&nbsp;<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Compile the solution. Now the proxy class is ready to be consumed =
by .NET=20
  clients. Which will be detailed in the next section.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Also following entries are made to the app.config for runtime use =
to=20
  identify the web service.<BR><BR><IMG width=3D"515" height=3D"89" =
alt=3D"9.gif" =
src=3D"http://csharpcorner.mindcrackerinc.netdna-cdn.com/UploadFile/chinn=
asrihari/consming-sap-web-services-and-net/Images/9.gif"=20
  border=3D"0"><BR></LI></OL></DIV>
<DIV><B>CONSUMING PROXY IN .NET CLIENT</B></DIV>
<DIV><BR></DIV>
<DIV>Follow the steps to create and read the data by using the=20
proxy.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<OL>
  <LI>Add a new 'ASP.NET Web application' to the SAPDotNetIntegration =
solution.=20
  And name it as AspDotNetClient.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Add the reference to the SAPWebServiceProxyLibrary.dll compiled =
and saved=20
  on the disk. By right clicking on the AspDotNetClient, and clicking on =
the=20
  'Add reference context' menu.<BR><BR></LI>
  <LI>Add the following statement to the code behind<BR><SPAN =
style=3D'color: blue; font-family: "Verdana","sans-serif"; font-size: =
10pt; mso-bidi-font-family: "Courier New"; mso-no-proof: yes;'><FONT=20
  class=3D"Apple-style-span" color=3D"#000000" face=3D"Verdana" =
size=3D"3"><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-size: 12px;"><BR></SPAN></FONT>using</SPAN><SPAN =
style=3D'font-family: "Verdana","sans-serif"; font-size: 10pt; =
mso-bidi-font-family: "Courier New"; mso-no-proof: yes;'>=20
  SAPWebServiceProxyLibrary.CustomerMasterNamespace;<BR><BR></SPAN></LI>
  <LI>Following are the basic lines of code to be written to asscess the =
data=20
  from SAP system.<BR><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"color: =
rgb(0, 128, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: =
13px;"><FONT=20
  class=3D"Apple-style-span" color=3D"#000000" face=3D"Verdana" =
size=3D"3"><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-size: 12px;"><BR></SPAN></FONT>//Creating the =
Service<FONT class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  face=3D"Verdana" size=3D"3"><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span" =
style=3D"font-size: 12px;"><BR></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN=20
  class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; =
font-size: 13px;"><SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: teal;">ZSN_WEBSERVICEService<BR></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">_proxy =
=3D <SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: blue;">new</SPAN> <SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: teal;">ZSN_WEBSERVICEService</SPAN>();<BR></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;"><SPAN =
style=3D"color: green;">//stores=20
  the return row XML data from the SAP web service<FONT =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  color=3D"#000000"><BR></FONT></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; =
font-size: 13px;"><SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: teal;"><FONT class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  color=3D"#000000"><BR></FONT>String</SPAN> outData;<BR></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;"><SPAN =
style=3D"mso-spacerun: yes;"><BR></SPAN><SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: green;">//Setting the User Credentials<FONT =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  face=3D"Verdana" size=3D"3"><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span" =
style=3D"font-size: 12px;"><BR></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN=20
  class=3D"Apple-style-span" style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; =
font-size: 13px;">_proxy.Credentials=20
  =3D <SPAN style=3D"color: blue;">new</SPAN> <SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: teal;">NetworkCredential</SPAN>(<SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: maroon;">"loginName"</SPAN>, <SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: maroon;">"password"</SPAN>);<BR></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"color: rgb(0, 128, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; =
font-size: 13px;">//We=20
  have a stateful communication therefore we have to use a
   //CookieContainer<BR></SPAN><SPAN style=3D'color: teal; font-family: =
"Verdana","sans-serif"; font-size: 10pt; mso-bidi-font-family: "Courier =
New"; mso-no-proof: yes;'>CookieContainer</SPAN><SPAN=20
  style=3D'font-family: "Verdana","sans-serif"; font-size: 10pt; =
mso-bidi-font-family: "Courier New"; mso-no-proof: yes;'>=20
  _cookie =3D <SPAN style=3D"color: blue;">new</SPAN> <SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: teal;">CookieContainer</SPAN>();<BR></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: =
13px;">_proxy.CookieContainer=20
  =3D _cookie;<BR></SPAN><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span" =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 128, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; =
font-size: 13px;">//=20
  p_filepath_app is the input parameter to identify the specific SAP web =
//=20
  service<FONT class=3D"Apple-style-span" face=3D"Verdana" =
size=3D"3"><SPAN class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-size: 12px;"><BR></SPAN></FONT></SPAN><SPAN =
class=3D"Apple-style-span"=20
  style=3D"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;">outData =
=3D=20
  _proxy.ZsnWebservice(<SPAN=20
  style=3D"color: =
maroon;">"xmlfilepathonthesapserver"</SPAN>);</SPAN></LI></OL></DIV>
<P></P></FONT></DIV>
